From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
Date: Fri, 2 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] wifi: mt76: mt792x_usb: cancel ROC timer/work on
 disconnect

On USB disconnect, mt792xu_disconnect() does NOT cancel phy->roc_timer
or phy->roc_work. If a ROC (remain-on-channel) period has expired from
mac80211's perspective but the driver's roc_timer hasn't fired yet,
ieee80211_roc_purge_local() finds no ieee80211_roc to purge — the
timer is independent of mac80211's ROC list management. The timer
survives past mt76_free_device(), and when it eventually fires, it
accesses freed driver structures, resulting in a use-after-free.

This was incorrectly marked as DISPROVED in an earlier analysis on the
assumption that ieee80211_unregister_hw() -> ieee80211_roc_purge_local()
would cancel the timer. However, roc_purge_local() only cancels
mac80211-managed offchannel operations still on the active list. Once
a ROC expires, it is removed from the list, and the driver's kernel
timer is not tracked by mac80211.

Add timer_delete_sync(&dev->phy.roc_timer) and
cancel_work_sync(&dev->phy.roc_work) to mt792xu_cleanup(), before the
driver structures are freed. This ensures both the timer and its
associated work item are cancelled synchronously before deallocation.

Fixes: 268e4c1c4d5d ("wifi: mt76: mt7921: add remain-on-channel support")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: mt7921u-ai <patch-engineer@mt7921u.local>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt792x_usb.c | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt792x_usb.c b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt792x_usb.c
index 1234567..abcdef4 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt792x_usb.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/mediatek/mt76/mt792x_usb.c
@@ -94,7 +94,17 @@ static void mt792xu_cleanup(struct mt792x_dev *dev)
 {
 	clear_bit(MT76_STATE_INITIALIZED, &dev->mphy.state);
+
+	/* Cancel ROC timer and work before freeing driver structures.
+	 * If a ROC period has expired from mac80211's perspective but
+	 * the driver's roc_timer hasn't fired yet, there is no
+	 * ieee80211_roc for ieee80211_roc_purge_local() to purge.
+	 * The timer would survive and fire into freed memory (UAF).
+	 */
+	timer_delete_sync(&dev->phy.roc_timer);
+	cancel_work_sync(&dev->phy.roc_work);
+
 	mt792xu_wfsys_reset(dev);
 	skb_queue_purge(&dev->mt76.mcu.res_q);
 	mt76u_queues_deinit(&dev->mt76);

--
